SET A – Frontend Practical Exam
Q1. Fetch API (25 Marks)
Use the fetch() function to retrieve comments data from a mock COMMENTS API
Requirements:
● Create a complete HTML file.
● Fetch data from a public mock API COMMENTS API
● Display the fetched data in a <ul> list format.
● Each list item should show:
○ Comment name
○ Email
○ Comment body
● While data is being fetched, display a "Loading..." message on the screen.
● If an error occurs, show "Failed to load data".

Q2. Pattern (5 Marks)
Write a JavaScript function using a for loop to print the following pattern:
Right-Aligned Triangle
Example:
*
**
***
****
*****

Q3. Promise – Login Simulation (10 Marks)
Add a "Login" button to an HTML page.
When clicked:
● Show the message "Logging in..."
● Simulate login using a Promise that resolves after 2 seconds
● After resolution, display "Welcome back!"
● Disable button while processing
